Step 1. Calculate the Gross Profit Margin.
• From the income statement, Gross Profit = 1,136,701.10 and Total Revenue = 6,836,701.10.
• Gross Profit Margin = (Gross Profit ÷ Total Revenue) × 100
  = (1,136,701.10 ÷ 6,836,701.10) × 100
  ≈ 16.63%

Step 2. Calculate the Operating Cash Flow Ratio.
• From the cash flow statement, Net Cash Flow from Operating Activities = –6,856,840.58.
• From the balance sheet, Total Current Liabilities = 1,601,835.08.
• Operating Cash Flow Ratio = Operating Cash Flow ÷ Current Liabilities
  = –6,856,840.58 ÷ 1,601,835.08
  ≈ –4.28

Thus, the answer is:
